DEBUG: upsert_asset values: ('cf385f59-9e7a-4c24-b06d-e240e01f21fe', '3d95540f-cda5-4e49-8069-3a2b4f3d19c9', 'slide_deck', 'completed', '["Create a 15-slide presentation in English based on the paper \'Fueling Organized Crime: The Mexican War on Drugs and Oil Theft\'. Use a professional academic tone.\\n\\nStructure:\\n1. Title Slide: Title and authors (Battiston, Daniele, Le Moglie, Pinotti).\\n2. Research Question & Motivation: Investigate if crackdowns on drugs unintentionally spur oil theft.\\n3. Theoretical Framework: The \'Leapfrogging\' model explaining why challenger cartels invest in new sectors.\\n4. Institutional Context I: The Mexican War on Drugs started by Calderón in 2007.\\n5. Institutional Context II: Large-scale oil theft via tapping Pemex pipelines.\\n6. Empirical Strategy: Regression Discontinuity Design (RDD) focusing on local political alignment.\\n7. Identification Strategy: Using PAN\'s margin of victory as the running variable to proxy crackdown intensity.\\n8. RDD Validity I: Balancing tests on predetermined characteristics (geography, population, etc.) from Table A.9.\\n9. RDD Validity II: McCrary density test to rule out manipulation of election results (Figure A.7).\\n10. RDD Validity III: Placebo test for the year 2006 to show no pre-existing effect before the War on Drugs (Table A.10).\\n11. RDD Main Results (Visual): Show the clear discontinuity in illegal taps at the cutoff (Figure 6).\\n12. RDD Main Results (Estimates): Quantify the effect (+6.6 taps/year) and discuss specifications from Table 3.\\n13. RDD Robustness I: Permutation tests with artificial cutoffs to confirm statistical significance (Figure A.10).\\n14. RDD Robustness II: Sensitivity analysis showing stability across different bandwidths and polynomials (Figure A.8).\\n15. Dynamic Effects & Policy Implications: Evolution of the effect over time (Figure 7) and the need for multi-sectoral enforcement.", \'en-US\', 2, 3]', None, {})
  [+] Notebook: Measuring Peer Effects through Natural Experiments: The 1980 Earthquake
